mean_en: a young animal or plant in the very early stages of development before birth, or before coming out of its egg or seed, especially a human egg in the first eight weeks after fertilization
sentence: Embryos take shape in the womb of a woman.
sentence_trans: 胚胎在女性的子宫里成形。
word_etyma: em使 + bry发芽 + o表名词 → embryo胚胎，萌芽
